Yes <@U04AQA0QM8E>, you're right. I think I'll settle for a custom property with the right formatting. Actually, talking with my PM, he said that he would need a prop with a bunch of deal props to show (probably crafted with some backend integration), so I created a multi line text prop for testing with this JSON structure
```{
  "module": [
    { "label": "AMOUNT", "value": "1.234,56" },
    { "label": "TAEG", "value": "6%" }
  ]
}```
 and read it from the email custom module like this
```{% set test = contact.test_multi_line_text | fromjson %}

&lt;ul&gt;
  {% for item in test.module %}
  &lt;li&gt;{{ item.label }}: {{ item.value }}&lt;/li&gt;
  {% endfor %}
&lt;/ul&gt;```
It works!

PS: I still have the programmable email option enabled, I guess it is required in order to use _fromjson_ filter on the prop, right?
Thank you.

